The paper discusses the interaction between humans and machines, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also presents a typology and framework for profiling human-machine networks, which involves the use of data and information systems (cs.SI) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the potential benefits and challenges of human-machine networks, which falls under the category of computer systems and networking (cs.CS) and systems and control (cs.SY).
